From: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
Subject: [PATCH 08/12] nvidia-390xx: fix list_is_head usage (kernel 6.9)

Kernel 6.9 added list_is_head() as a required internal for some list
traversal macros that the nvidia-390xx driver uses in its own list
implementation. Older kernels don't have list_is_head().

Also fixes 'struct vm_fault' field renames for fault handler in 6.9.

Signed-off-by: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
---
diff --git a/kernel/nvidia/nv-list.h b/kernel/nvidia/nv-list.h
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/kernel/nvidia/nv-list.h
@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@
+#pragma once
+#include <linux/version.h>
+#include <linux/list.h>
+
+/* list_is_head() was added in kernel 5.15 upstream but is used
+   by some internal macros that 390xx tries to redefine.
+   Provide compat for anything < 5.15 and guard against double-def. */
+#ifndef list_is_head
+static inline int list_is_head(const struct list_head *list,
+                                const struct list_head *head)
+{
+    return list->next == head->next && list->prev == head;
+}
+#endif
+
+/* kernel 6.9 vm_fault field rename */
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6, 9, 0)
+#define NV_VM_FAULT_ADDRESS(vmf) ((vmf)->real_address)
+#else
+#define NV_VM_FAULT_ADDRESS(vmf) ((vmf)->address)
+#endif
